# TypeScript strict typing

> **Non-negotiable:** correct types everywhere. No escape hatches without user approval.

## Required dev dependency

Root and every Node package (`apps/cli`, `apps/playground`, `scripts/`) MUST declare:

```json
"@types/node": "^22.15.21"
```

`scripts/tsconfig.json` MUST include:

```json
"types": ["node"],
"lib": ["ES2022"]
```

Without `@types/node`, `process`, `node:fs`, and `node:path` fail typecheck in IDE and `tsc -p scripts/tsconfig.json`.

## No `any` or `unknown`

| Rule | Requirement |
|------|-------------|
| `any` | **Forbidden** — use concrete types, generics, or unions |
| `unknown` | **Forbidden** — narrow at boundaries with type guards |
| `JSON.parse` | Parse into `object`, validate with a type guard, then return typed value |
| Promise `.catch` | Use `exitWithError(reason: Error \| string \| number \| boolean \| object)` — see `scripts/lib/errors.ts` |
| ESLint | `@typescript-eslint/no-explicit-any`, `no-unsafe-*` — **0 errors** |

### Allowed boundary patterns

```typescript
// JSON boundary — immediate narrow, no lingering any/unknown
function parseJsonObject(raw: string): object {
  const parsed = JSON.parse(raw) as string | number | boolean | object | null;
  if (typeof parsed !== 'object' || parsed === null) {
    throw new Error('Expected JSON object');
  }
  return parsed;
}

// Rejection boundary — no unknown annotation
main().catch(exitWithError);
```

## Verification

```bash
pnpm typecheck:scripts   # scripts/**/*.ts
pnpm lint                # includes scripts with strictTypeChecked
pnpm verify
```

## Agent MUST NOT

- Add `@types/node` only in a child package when root `scripts/` also use Node APIs
- Annotate catch handlers as `unknown`
- Use `as any` to silence type errors
- Disable `no-explicit-any` without user approval
